	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I don't think it's an issue of schools <em>against</em> teaching C, it's that back in the late 90s/early 2000s, Sun really forced (bought) their way into academia and pushed Java big time.  Colleges and universities latched on, and you ended up with trash like the APCS/CSAP exams being done exclusively in Java.  Microsoft has done similarly with C#.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


