		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How is that different in practice from needing the non-free Windows operating system to run your hardware drivers? This can happen when no laptops in your local Best Buy have a penguin logo to imply that free drivers are available for the hardware, and System76 (which specializes in Linux PCs) doesn't offer any laptops in your preferred form factor. <a href="https://wiki.debian.org/InstallingDebianOn/Asus/T100TA" class="postlink">ASUS T100 still has no suspend on Linux after years</a>.<br /><br />Even if Windows is non-free as in speech, Linux is non-free as in beer because of increased hardware support cost for the manufacturer. Last I checked, the Dell XPS 13 with Windows 10 Home sold for $50 less than the same laptop with Ubuntu.

		

